<title>UK: Ex-dividends to take 3.38 points off FTSE, May 12.</title>
<headline>Ex-dividends to take 3.38 points off FTSE, May 12.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The following FTSE-100 stocks will trade ex-dividend on May 12 and analysts estimate this will take 3.38 points off the index that day.</p>
<p>						   DIVIDEND	INDEX</p>
<p>						   (PENCE)	 EFFECT</p>
<p>	     COMPANY			  Net    Gross   Gross</p>
<p>    * British Petroleum		   5.25   6.563   2.166</p>
<p>    * General Accident		   22.85  28.563   0.800</p>
<p>    * Redland				11.17  13.963   0.419</p>
